data.enText: ducks
or
duck

data.chText: 鸭
data.enText: a common bird that lives on or near water and has short legs, webbed feet (= feet with thin pieces of skin between the toes) and a wide beak. There are many types of duck , some of which are kept for their meat or eggs.

data.chText: 野鸭
data.enText: wild ducks

data.chText: 鸭蛋
data.enText: duck eggs

data.chText: 母鸭
data.enText: a female duck

data.chText: 鸭肉
data.enText: meat from a duck

data.chText: 烤鸭蘸橘子酱
data.enText: roast duck with orange sauce
duckie
ducks
ducky

data.chText: （表示友好的称呼）乖乖，宝贝儿
data.enText: a friendly way of addressing sb

data.chText: 还有别的事吗，宝贝儿？
data.enText: Anything else, duck?

data.chText: 零分
data.enText: a batsman's score of zero

data.chText: 他因得了零分而出局。
data.enText: He was out for a duck.
get/have (all) your ducks in a row

data.chText: 为某事做充分准备；把事情安排得井井有条
data.enText: to have made all the preparations needed to do sth; to be well organized
(take to sth) like a duck to water

data.chText: 像鸭子入水般容易，轻而易举，毫不困难，毫无畏惧（习惯于某事）
data.enText: (to become used to sth) very easily, without any problems or fears

data.chText: 她教起书来驾轻就熟。
data.enText: She has taken to teaching like a duck to water.
(like) water off a duck's back

data.chText: （像）耳边风；水过鸭背
data.enText: used to say that sth, especially criticism, has no effect on sb/sth

data.chText: 我无法告诉我儿子该做什么，他根本听不进去。
data.enText: I can't tell my son what to do; it's water off a duck's back with him.

data.chText: 低下头，弯下身（以免被打中或看见）
data.enText: to move your head or body downwards to avoid being hit or seen

data.chText: 他穿过门口时得弯下身来。
data.enText: He had to duck as he came through the door.

data.chText: 我们弓身躲在墙后不让他们看见。
data.enText: We ducked down behind the wall so they wouldn't see us.

data.chText: 他总算躲开了别人的视线。
data.enText: He just managed to duck out of sight .

data.chText: 她低着头进了汽车。
data.enText: She ducked her head and got into the car.

data.chText: 躲闪；躲避
data.enText: to avoid sth by moving your head or body out of the way

data.chText: 他躲开最先几拳后便开始反击。
data.enText: He ducked the first few blows then started to fight back.

data.chText: 迅速行进，飞快行走（以免被看见）
data.enText: to move somewhere quickly, especially in order to avoid being seen

data.chText: 我们进来时她转身躲进了隔壁房间。
data.enText: She ducked into the adjoining room as we came in.

data.chText: 逃避，回避，推脱，推诿（职责或责任）
data.enText: to avoid a difficult or unpleasant duty or responsibility

data.chText: 轮到他做晚饭了，但我敢打赌他会想方设法逃避的。
data.enText: It's his turn to cook dinner, but I bet he'll try to duck out of it.

data.chText: 政府在回避这个问题。
data.enText: The government is ducking the issue.
dunk

data.chText: 把…按入水中
data.enText: to push sb underwater and hold them there for a short time

data.chText: 孩子们在池塘里相互把对方按入水中。
data.enText: The kids were ducking each other in the pool.

tr: small wild or domesticated web-footed broad-billed swimming bird usually having a depressed body and short legs
a heavy cotton fabric of plain weave
flesh of a duck (domestic or wild)
(cricket) a score of nothing by a batsman
avoid or try to avoid fulfilling, answering, or performing (duties, questions, or issues)
example: They tend to evade their responsibilities

tr: to move (the head or body) quickly downwards or away
example: Before he could duck, another stone struck him

value.def: A duck is a very common water bird with short legs, a short neck, and a large flat beak.

example.ex: Chickens and ducks scratch around the outbuildings.
example.tran: 鸡鸭在棚子周围到处乱刨。

posc.def: Duck is the flesh of this bird when it is eaten as food.

value.def: A duck is a female duck. The male is called a drake.

example.ex: I brought in one drake and three ducks.
example.tran: 我弄来一只公鸭和三只母鸭。

value.def: If you duck, you move your head or the top half of your body quickly downwards to avoid something that might hit you, or to avoid being seen.

example.ex: He ducked in time to save his head from a blow from the poker...
example.tran: 他及时低下头，躲过了拨火棍的击打。

example.ex: He ducked his head to hide his admiration...
example.tran: 他低下头以掩饰他的仰慕之情。

example.ex: I wanted to duck down and slip past but they saw me.
example.tran: 我本想弯腰溜过去，但被他们看到了。

value.tran: 急速低头（或弓身）(以免被打中或看见)

value.def: If you duck something such as a blow, you avoid it by moving your head or body quickly downwards.

example.tran: 汉斯灵巧地躲过他们的击打。

value.tran: (快速低头或弓身以)躲闪,闪避

value.def: If you duck into a place, you move there quickly, often in an attempt to avoid danger or to avoid being seen.

example.tran: 马特慌忙躲进他的办公室。

example.ex: He ducked through the door and looked about frantically.
example.tran: 他溜进门里，慌忙地四处张望着。

value.def: You say that someone ducks a duty or responsibility when you disapprove of the fact that they avoid it.

example.ex: The Opposition reckons the Health Secretary has ducked all the difficult decisions...
example.tran: 反对党认为卫生大臣逃避了所有决策难题。

example.ex: He had ducked the confrontation with United Nations inspectors last summer.
example.tran: 去年夏天他避开了与联合国核查人员的对峙。

value.tran: 逃避,回避,推脱,推诿(义务或责任)

value.def: If someone ducks someone else, they force them or their head under water for a short time.

example.ex: She splashed around in the pool with Mark, rowdily trying to duck him.
example.tran: 她和马克在水池中嬉戏,胡闹着要将他按入水中。

value.tran: 将(某人或其头部)按入水中

value.def: Some people call other people duck or ducks as a sign of affection.

example.ex: Oh, I am glad to see you, duck.
example.tran: 噢,很高兴见到你,亲爱的。

value.def: You say that criticism is like water off a duck's back or water off a duck's back to emphasize that it is not having any effect on the person being criticized.

example.ex: All the criticism is water off a duck's back to me.
example.tran: 批评对我来说左耳进右耳出，毫无影响。

value.tran: 毫无效果的;不起作用的

value.def: If you take to something like a duck to water, you discover that you are naturally good at it or that you find it very easy to do.

example.ex: She took to mothering like a duck to water.
example.tran: 她很快就对母亲这一角色驾轻就熟了。

value.tran: 很自然地就会;轻而易举;如鱼得水
